{"id":"math/9201218","submitter":null,"authors":"Keith Ball","title":"The plank problem for symmetric bodies","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1007/BF01245089","report-no":"Banach Archive 9/25/90","categories":"math.MG math.FA","license":null,"abstract":"  Given a symmetric convex body $C$ and $n$ hyperplanes in an Euclidean space,\nthere is a translate of a multiple of $C$, at least ${1\\over n+1}$ times as\nlarge, inside $C$, whose interior does not meet any of the hyperplanes. The\nresult generalizes Bang's solution of the plank problem of Tarski and has\napplications to Diophantine approximation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 25 Sep 1990 14:45:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-10-22"}
